Attaching volumes to an EC2 instance.

On Instance create, add volume.
Specify what snapshot you want.
The console will give you a path for the volume, like /dev/sda.

lsblk
ls -l /dev/s*

sudo mkdir /<newmountpoint>
sudo mount /dev/<path> /<newmountpoint>

ls -al /dev/disk/by-uuid/
edit /etc/fstab to mount on startup
findmnt --verify

